member.name: T:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder
member.summary:
name fo well-known-folders in a outlook mailboxes
Outlook creates certain folders for users by default. Instead of using the corresponding folder id value, for convenience, you can use the well-known folder names from the table below when accessing these folders.
For example, you can get the Drafts folder using its well-known name with the following query.

member.summary: The archive folder messages are sent to when using the One_Click Archive feature in Outlook clients that support it. Note: this is not the same as the Archive Mailbox feature of Exchange online.

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.conflicts
member.summary: The folder that contains conflicting items in the mailbox.

member.summary: The folder items are moved to when they are deleted.

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.drafts
member.summary: The folder that contains unsent messages.

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.inbox

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.junkemail
member.summary: The junk email folder.

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.msgfolderroot

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.outbox

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.recoverableitemsdeletions
member.summary: The folder that contains soft-deleted items: deleted either from the Deleted Items folder, or by pressing shift+delete in Outlook. This folder is not visible in any Outlook email client, but end users can interact with it through the Recover Deleted Items from Server feature in Outlook or Outlook on the web.

member.name: F:MSGraph.Exchange.Mail.WellKnownFolder.scheduled
